This paper deals with network security and forensic analysis, which falls under the category of "Computer Science and Security" (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on DNS tunneling techniques, which are used in network communication, making "Computer Networks and Communications" (cs.NI) another likely sub-category. The paper also uses entropy distribution averaging to predict network protocols, which involves statistical analysis and machine learning, making "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS) possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents a method for automating forensic analysis, which involves software engineering and system design, making "Software Engineering" (cs.SE) another possible sub-category.
